# Google Sheets Integration — Faturamento Dashboard
#
# 1. Enable "Google Sheets API v4" in Google Cloud Console:
#    https://console.cloud.google.com → APIs & Services → Enable APIs
#
# 2. Create an API Key (no OAuth required for read-only access):
#    Google Cloud Console → APIs & Services → Credentials → Create credentials → API Key
#    Restrict it to: Sheets API v4, and your deployment domain.
#
# 3. Open the FATURAMENTO spreadsheet and set sharing to
#    "Anyone with the link can view" (does NOT need to be public/indexed).
#
# 4. Copy this file to .env.local and fill in the values below.
#    .env.local is git-ignored and never committed.
#
# When both variables are set, the dashboard fetches live data from Google Sheets.
# When either is missing, the dashboard falls back to the built-in mock data.

VITE_GOOGLE_SHEETS_ID=1tQHfqn8VSS78iQ7csxwJ6xobT769Umc5-ZDkqLXTjps
VITE_GOOGLE_SHEETS_API_KEY=your_api_key_here
